      • getFirstCellNum

        int getFirstCellNum()
        Get column number of first cell. Workbooks have an area of used cells. All cells outside of that area are blank. If the value returned by this method is greater than 0 that means that all the cells to the left of the column returned are blank. The opposite is not necessarily true, since the area of used cells might not be updated when a cell is cleared (because that would require a full sweep of all rows).
        Returns:
        number of first cell that potentially contains a value.

      • getLastCellNum

        int getLastCellNum()
        Get column number of last cell. Workbooks have an area of used cells. All cells outside of that area are blank. If the value returned by this method is less than the number of columns-1 that means that all the cells to the right of the column returned are blank. The opposite is not necessarily true, since the area of used cells might not be updated when a cell is cleared (because that would require a full sweep of all rows).
        Returns:
        number of last cell that potentially contains a value.
